problem: Let $x$ and $y$ be real numbers satisfying $x^4y^5+y^4x^5=810$ and $x^3y^6+y^3x^6=945$. Evaluate $2x^3+(xy)^3+2y^3$.
solution: Factoring $x^4y^4$ and $x^3y^3$ from the left-hand sides of the two equations, respectively, we get \[\begin{aligned} x^4y^4(x+y) &= 810, \\ x^3y^3(x^3+y^3) &= 945. \end{aligned}\]Let $s = x+y$ and $p = xy.$ Then we can rewrite the given equations as \[\begin{aligned} p^4s &= 810, \\ p^3(s^3-3ps) &= 945,\end{aligned}\]using $x^3+y^3 = (x+y)^3 - 3xy(x+y) = s^3 - 3ps$. Substituting $s = 810/p^4$ into the second equation, we get \[\begin{aligned} p^3\left(\frac{810^3}{p^{12}} - 3p \cdot \frac{810}{p^4}\right) &= 945 \\ \frac{810^3}{p^9} - 3 \cdot 810 &= 945 \\ p^9 &= \frac{810^3}{3 \cdot 810 + 945} = \frac{810^3}{15^3} = 54^3. \end{aligned}\]Thus $p = \sqrt[3]{54},$ and $s = 810/p^4 = 810/(54\sqrt[3]{54}) = 15/\sqrt[3]{54}.$ The quantity we want to compute is then \[\begin{aligned} 2x^3 + (xy)^3 + 2y^3 &= 2(s^3 - 3ps) + p^3 \\ &= 2s^3 - 6ps + p^3 \\ &= 2 \cdot \frac{15^3}{54} - 6 \cdot \sqrt[3]{54} \cdot \frac{15}{\sqrt[3]{54}} + 54 \\ &= 125 - 90 + 54 \\ &= \boxed{89}. \end{aligned}\]
model_solution:
Step 1: Let $a=x^3y^6$ and $b=y^3x^6$.
Then $x^3y^6+y^3x^6=a+b$ and $x^4y^5+y^4x^5=\frac{a}{xy}+\frac{b}{xy}=\frac{a+b}{xy}$.
Since we are given that $a+b=945$ and $\frac{a+b}{xy}=810$, we have $\frac{a+b}{xy}=810$
Step 2: $810xy=945$
$\Rightarrow xy=\frac{945}{810}$
$\Rightarrow xy=\frac{7}{6}$
Step 3: $\frac{a+b}{xy}=810$
$\Rightarrow \frac{945}{\frac{7}{6}}=810$
$\Rightarrow 5=5$
Step 4: Factor $x^3y^6+y^3x^6$ as $(xy)^3(x+y)$ and $x^4y^5+y^4x^5$ as $(xy)^3(x^3y^2+y^3x^2)$.
Then $(xy)^3(x+y)=945$ and $(xy)^3(x^3y^2+y^2x^2)=810(xy)^3$.
$(xy)^3(x^3y^2+y^2x^2)=810(xy)^3$
$\Rightarrow (x^3y^2+y^2x^2)=810$
$(xy)^3(x+y)=945$
$\Rightarrow (xy)^3\left(\frac{2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)}{2}\right)=945$
$(xy)^3\left(\frac{2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)}{2}\right)=945$
$\Rightarrow (xy)^3\left(\frac{2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)}{2}\right)=945$
$\Rightarrow (xy)^3(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2))=1890$
$\Rightarrow 2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)=\frac{1890}{(xy)^3}$
$\Rightarrow 2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)=2\cdot 2x^3+2\cdot 2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)$
$2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)=2(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2))-(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2))$
$2(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2))-(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2))=2\left(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)\right)-\left(2x^3+2y^3+3xy(x^2+y^2)\right)$
